<h2>Concept &amp; massing models</h2>
<p>Simplified block models used during early design stages to study scale, height, form, and spatial relationships. They're perfect for concept presentations, entitlement meetings, and planning reviews — where the goal is to communicate intent quickly without unnecessary detail.</p>
<h2>Presentation models</h2>
<p>Detailed architectural replicas highlighting façade treatment, materials, glazing, and structural expression. These are ideal for client presentations, sales centers, and public exhibitions, where finish and realism carry the message.</p>
<h2>Masterplan &amp; site models</h2>
<p>Large-scale models for multi-building developments, showing massing, circulation, landscape, and site relationships. They work well for real-estate presentations, planning reviews, and public exhibitions of larger projects.</p>
<h2>Interior models</h2>
<p>Built at a larger scale to communicate units, hotel rooms, and interior spaces — useful when the experience of a space, not just its exterior form, is what needs to be sold or approved.</p>
